  "text": "Antibodies to the peptide showing homology with an amino acid sequence of plasminogen-binding protein (anti-PBP) may have increased sensitivities of 93-95% for autoimmune pancreatitis [CITATION_1] . These antibodies were found in patients who were serum IgG4-negative, suggesting that they may be useful for Type 2 AIP and the cohort of Type 1 AIP with negative serology. However, 5% of patients with pancreatic cancer also had positive anti-PBP serology, preventing its use in discriminating AIP from cancer [CITATION_2] .",
